compute normalized differences (feature engineering the band data)

Choosing to use normalized differences because they account for differences in light intensity, etc per satellite image. Not good to feed raw band data into a model when comparing across images.

Based on plots of the radiometer scans, I can see that the algae differ from the white snow the most in the B3-B6 range, so I will compute the normalized differences in that range.

nd <- function(a,b) (a-b)/(a+b) # normalized difference function

as_nd <- as_band %>% 
  select(scan_id, sample_id, b3:b6) %>% 
  # compute 6 potential variables to use for algae abundance model. 
  mutate(rgnd = nd(b4, b3),
         ndvi = nd(b5, b4),
         b6b5 = nd(b6, b5),
         b5b3 = nd(b5, b3),
         b6b3 = nd(b6, b3),
         b6b4 = nd(b6, b4), .keep="unused")

compute mean values for model

joined_stats <- joined %>% 
  mutate(cells_in_sample = cells_per_ul * total_sample_water_vol_ul) %>% # normalized cell density per total sample volume
  select(sample_id, 
         ndvi, rgnd, b6b5, b5b3, b6b3, b6b4,
         albedo, 
         frac_red, inorganic_carbon_mg, organic_carbon_mg, nitrogen_mg, cell_cm2_per_l, cells_in_sample) %>% 
  group_by(sample_id) %>% 
  summarize(across(everything(), list(mean = mean, sd = sd), .names = "{.col}_{.fn}")) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  select(-contains("mg_sd")) #since n=1, all SD of biomass measurements is 0
joined_stats

my_plot <- function(df, y, x, title){
  y <- enquo(y)
  x <- enquo(x)
  df %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y = !!y, x = !!x)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_text(aes(label = sample_id)) +
    ggtitle(title)
}

# variable importance
my_plot_var <- function(df, var){
  var <- enquo(var)
  
  df %>% 
    mutate(sample_id = sample_id %>% fct_reorder(!!var)) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y =!!var, x = sample_id)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    coord_flip() +
    ylab(as_label(var))
}

my_plot_crossbars <- function(dat, y_mean, y_sd, x_mean, x_sd, tag){
  x_mean <- enquo(x_mean)
  x_sd <- enquo(x_sd)
  y_mean <- enquo(y_mean)
  y_sd <- enquo(y_sd)

  dat %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y = !!y_mean, x = !!x_mean)) + 
    geom_pointrange(aes(ymin = !!y_mean - !!y_sd, 
                        ymax = !!y_mean + !!y_sd),
                    alpha = 0.4) +
    geom_linerange(aes(xmin = !!x_mean - !!x_sd,
                       xmax = !!x_mean + !!x_sd),
                    alpha = 0.4) +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(tag = tag)
}

Present models in table

get_formula <- function(mod){
  call <- mod$call %>% as.character()
  call[2]
}

tidy(area_mod) %>% add_column(formula = get_formula(area_mod), .before=1)

make_entry <- function(mod){
  tidy(mod) %>% 
    add_column(formula = get_formula(mod), .before=1)
}
mod_results <- bind_rows(
  make_entry(area_mod),
  make_entry(toc_mod),
  make_entry(nitrogen_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_rgnd_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_area_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_carbon_mod)
)

  kbl(caption = "Model results") %>%
